{{Infobox academic conference | title = British Gravity Meeting | logo = [[File:BritGrav logo.png|300px|British Gravity (BritGrav) Meeting logo. First used for BritGrav 14.]] | abbreviation = BritGrav | discipline = [[gravity|Gravitational physics]] | publisher = | history = 2001– | frequency = Annual | website = [https://sites.google.com/port.ac.uk/britgrav18/home BritGrav 18] }}
'''BritGrav ''' ('''British Gravity Meeting''') is an annual [[Academic conference|meeting]], based in the [[United Kingdom]] and [[Republic of Ireland|Ireland]], for academics whose research is connected to [[gravitation]]. The meeting covers a broad range of topics, including [[general relativity]], [[quantum gravity]], [[gravitational-wave detector|gravitational-wave detection]] and [[gravitational-wave astronomy|astronomy]], the [[astrophysics]] of [[black hole]]s and [[neutron star]]s, [[cosmology]], and [[Experimental physics|experimentation]].
Many of the talks are given by [[Postdoctoral research|postdocs]] and [[Doctor of Philosophy|graduate students]], and are between 10 and 20 minutes. During BritGrav 15 at the [[University of Birmingham]] in 2015, 78% of the talks were by students and 18% were by post-docs.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Berry|first1=Christopher|title=BritGrav 15|url=http://cplberry.com/2015/05/05/britgrav15/|accessdate=14 October 2015}}</ref>
The first meeting was held at the [[University of Southampton]] in 2001.<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Gundlach|first1=C|title=The first BritGrav meeting|pages=arXiv:gr–qc/0104062|year= 2001|arxiv = gr-qc/0104062|bibcode = 2001gr.qc.....4062G}}</ref> The 2015 meeting was organised by the [[University of Birmingham]]; following the close of the meeting, there was a public lecture on [[Gravitational-wave observatory|gravitational-wave detection]] by [[James Hough]].<ref name=BritGrav15Outreach>{{cite web|title=Public Outreach|url=http://www.sr.bham.ac.uk/britgrav15/outreach.php|website=BritGrav 15|publisher=[[University of Birmingham]]|accessdate=11 February 2015}}</ref> The most recent meeting was at the [[University of Portsmouth]] from 18–19 April 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=BritGrav 18|url=https://sites.google.com/port.ac.uk/britgrav18/|publisher=[[University of Portsmouth]]|accessdate=19 March 2018}}</ref>
