'''Meer Uitgebreid Lager Onderwijs''' ([[Dutch language|Dutch]], "more advanced primary education") was during part of the twentieth century a level of education in the Netherlands (and the [[Dutch East Indies]]<ref>{{cite book |title=Upuleru |last=Siwabessy |first=G.A. |authorlink=G.A. Siwabessy |year=1979 |publisher=PT Gunung Agung |location=[[Jakarta]] |isbn= |language=Indonesian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://pakguruonline.pendidikan.net/sjh_pdd_sumbar_bab3a.html |title=Pendidikan Pemerintah Hindia Belanda |author= |year=2010 |work= |publisher=PakGuru Online |accessdate=19 August 2012}}</ref>), comparable with the [[junior high school]] level in the US education system. Its successors were the mavo and vbo, now both replaced by [[Voorbereidend middelbaar beroepsonderwijs|vmbo]]. This level of education still exists in [[Suriname]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://taalunieversum.org/onderwijs/termen/term/574/mulo/ |title=Meer Uitgebreid Lager Onderwijs |author= |year= |work= |publisher=Taalunieversum |accessdate=18 May 2017}}</ref>
