The '''Organization of Asia-Pacific News Agencies''' ('''OANA''') is an association of [[news agency|news agencies]] from [[UNESCO]] ([[United Nations]] Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization) member states in the Asia-Pacific region. It was previously known as the '''Organisation of Asian News Agencies'''.
It was formed in 1961 on UNESCO’s initiative. It provides a [[news]] wire service containing articles donated by its members.
