{{Infobox school |image = |imagesize = 200px |name = Terra Santa College |native_name = <small>Κολέγιο Τέρρα Σάντα ([[Greek language|Greek]])</small> |motto = ''S. Mons Sion in Jerusalem'' |founder = |headteacher = |chairperson = |established = 1641 |type = selective co-educational school |information = (+357) 22421100 |website = http://www.terrasantacyprus.com/ |teaching_staff = |age range = 4-18 |city = Nicosia |country = {{CYP}} }}
The '''Terra Santa College''' is the oldest school of Cyprus.
==History== [[File:Collegio Terra Santa.jpg|thumb|Collegio di Terra Santa|thumb|right|280px|Terra Santa College - [[Nicosia]]]] In 1646, the [[Custody of the Holy Land]], the order of the Franciscan monks that is situated in Jerusalem founded the Terra Santa College in Nicosia, Cyprus. Their main principles were Virtue, Diligence and Creativity. Initially the college operated as a Primary School, while in 1913 it broadened its horizons with the creation of the Secondary School. In 1970 the operation of the Nursery School commenced, bringing our school to the current form which comprises Primary and Secondary education. The main attribute of the school is multiculturalism.
The 28 January 2013, Terra Santa School and [[University of Cyprus]] signed an agreement that recognize Terra Santa School as prototype and experimental model school of the University of Cyprus.
[[File:Collegio di Terra Santa. Accordo con Universita di Cipro.JPG|thumb|Collegio di Terra Santa|thumb|middle|280px|The signing of the agreement with the [[University of Cyprus]]]]
